race.comment: Consistent mare SPECK (4) wasn't the best away so did a good job to be beaten just 1.5 lengths last start over 1000m at Scone. Competitive at Dubbo the run prior in a $75k open sprint so she can cope with this class. ZOE SHARK (2) added to a fine record over this specialist distance when narrowly defeated at Newcastle two back. Good effort to finish third off a seven-week let-up at Scone last time. Fitter and makes plenty of appeal. SARATOGA POWER (5) cruised to victory here at this distance two back before a moderate effort over 1100m at Scone most recently. Has won three from four here so back to 900m he is a major player. Ex WA sprinter REAL DELUXE (9) returns from a three-month spell for new trainer Paul Theobald. Betting should tell the story. WHO GOES THERE (1) won over 950m at Moree two back to chalk up the hat trick. Didn't measure up in town last time but can make amends.
